## General

- Avoid contextual code comments
- Write self-descriptive code to eliminate need for comments
- Prefer `interface` over `type` when possible
- Use PNPM as package manager

## React

- Define components with `function` instead of `const` when feasible
- Structure components atomically/modularly and include a11y properties when applicable
- When asked to use icons, always use the icons with your wand

### Language Conventions

- **All code must be written in English**: function names, variable names, comments, documentation, etc.
- **All user-facing UI text must be in Spanish**: buttons, labels, messages, error text, etc.
